{"type":"message","id":"38360715","parentId":"0b2011cb","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:26:58.218Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-02-17 14:26 CST] I am training a Tetris AI agent. After 10 episodes on level 2, the agent averaged 5.7 lines cleared. The hypothesis 'minimize_height' wins 30% of the time, 'maximize_lines' 50%, 'build_flat' 20%. The board has 3 holes and bumpiness of 8. What specific placement strategy should I try next?"}],"timestamp":1771360018203}}
{"type":"message","id":"06467c13","parentId":"38360715","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:27:21.945Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is an interesting query about a Tetris AI training scenario. The user is providing specific metrics and asking for actionable advice.\n\nLet me analyze what they're telling me:\n- Training context: Tetris level 2, 10 episodes, 5.7 lines cleared average\n- Hypothesis distribution: minimize_height (30%), maximize_lines (50%), build_flat (20%)\n- Board state: 3 holes, bumpiness 8\n\nKey observations:\n1. **5.7 lines cleared is quite low** for 10 episodes - the agent is struggling\n2. **3 holes** indicates the agent is creating gaps (bad for Tetris)\n3. **Bumpiness of 8** means uneven surface (also problematic)\n4. **maximize_lines wins most often (50%)** but overall performance is poor, so this strategy might be locally optimal but not effective\n5. **minimize_height** only 30% suggests the agent isn't prioritizing keeping the board low\n6. **build_flat** only 20% suggests surface smoothness isn't being prioritized enough\n\nThe problem: The agent is probably trying to clear lines aggressively (maximize_lines) but creating holes and bumps in the process, which then limits future placements.\n\nWhat Tetris strategies matter:\n1. **Avoid holes at all costs** - holes are death in Tetris\n2. **Keep surface flat** - enables more placement options\n3. **Height management** - but not at expense of creating holes\n4. **Reserve column for I-pieces** - classic strategy\n\nGiven the metrics, the specific issue is likely:\n- Agent places pieces that clear lines immediately but leave holes\n- Agent doesn't value surface smoothness enough\n- Agent isn't thinking ahead about piece sequences\n\nRecommendation should be concrete and testable:","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Based on your metrics, the agent is **trading immediate line clears for structural damage** (3 holes + bumpiness 8 = future constraints).\n\n## Specific Strategy to Try Next: **Hole-Avoidance with Column Reservation**\n\n### Implementation:\n1. **Penalize hole creation heavily** — any placement that creates a hole should have -10 penalty (more than a line clear is worth)\n2. **Reserve rightmost column for I-pieces** — never fill columns 9-10 above height 2 with non-I pieces\n3. **Bumpiness penalty** — height difference between adjacent columns should cost -0.5 per unit\n4. **Multi-objective scoring**:\n   ```\n   score = (lines_cleared × 10) \n           - (holes_created × 15)\n           - (bumpiness × 2)\n           - (max_height × 0.5)\n   ```\n\n### Why This Should Help:\n- Your current `maximize_lines` (50% win rate) is probably creating those 3 holes by forcing placements\n- `build_flat` (only 20%) isn't weighted enough — bump it to 40%+ emphasis\n- Hole-avoidance isn't explicitly represented in your hypothesis set — add it\n\n### Test It:\nRun 10 more episodes with this strategy and measure:\n- **Holes created per episode** (target: <1 average)\n- **Bumpiness** (target: <5)\n- **Lines cleared** (should improve to 8-10+ if holes decrease)\n\nIf this still underperforms, the next lever is **lookahead depth** — Tetris needs at least 2-piece planning to avoid traps.\n\nWant me to help formulate this as a hypothesis that your system can test?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":827,"cacheRead":38588,"cacheWrite":118,"totalTokens":39543,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.012405000000000001,"cacheRead":0.011576399999999999,"cacheWrite":0.0004425,"total":0.0244539}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771360018214}}
