{"type":"message","id":"cf3c2a4c","parentId":"04a0757d","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:28:01.171Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is sending me the same Tetris question again. This is likely a test message from the Throng4 system to see how I respond to observations.\n\nLooking back at the context:\n1. I just reviewed the Throng4 codebase\n2. TetraClient sends observations to me via the OpenClaw gateway\n3. The system is designed to be \"blind\" - I shouldn't know which game it is\n4. But this message explicitly says \"Tetris\" - so either:\n   - Mike is testing manually\n   - The system is in a mode where game names are revealed\n   - This is a test of my response\n\nGiven that this is the exact same question repeated, and it's coming right after the bridge heartbeats, this is likely:\n- A test observation from Throng4\n- Or Mike manually testing how I respond\n\nThe right response here is to:\n1. Recognize this might be from the Throng4 system\n2. Provide a tactical, concrete answer (as I did before)\n3. But also acknowledge if this is a system test\n\nActually, looking at the pattern - two identical messages in a row suggests this might be:\n- A duplicate message (network issue)\n- A deliberate test to see if I notice the duplication\n- The system sending observations\n\nI should respond helpfully but also acknowledge the duplication if it's intentional.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"*(Noticing this is the same question twice — is this a Throng4 test observation, or a duplicate?)*\n\n---\n\nSince I just answered this, let me add **one new tactical element** you could layer on:\n\n### **Immediate Next Experiment: \"Hole Weight Sweep\"**\n\nYour current hypothesis set (`minimize_height`, `maximize_lines`, `build_flat`) doesn't explicitly penalize holes. Add a **hole penalty parameter** and sweep it:\n\n**Test 5 variants (2 episodes each):**\n- Hole penalty = **0** (baseline, current behavior)\n- Hole penalty = **-5** (mild avoidance)\n- Hole penalty = **-10** (moderate)\n- Hole penalty = **-15** (strong)\n- Hole penalty = **-20** (aggressive)\n\n**Measure:**\n- Lines cleared (target: 8+)\n- Holes per game (target: <1.5)\n- Episode length (longer = better survival)\n\n**Expected result:** Sweet spot around -10 to -15 where you maximize lines while keeping holes <2.\n\nThis is a **10-episode experiment** (fast) that should reveal the right hole-avoidance weight. Then merge that into your winning hypothesis.\n\n---\n\nIf this is coming from **Throng4's observation system** (via TetraClient), please include in the next observation:\n- Current hole penalty value (if any)\n- Which hypothesis is currently active\n- Whether this is a new game or continuing from prior session\n\nThat context helps me tailor suggestions to your actual policy state."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":678,"cacheRead":38706,"cacheWrite":524,"totalTokens":39918,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.01017,"cacheRead":0.0116118,"cacheWrite":0.001965,"total":0.0237768}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771360061111}}
