{"type":"message","id":"c43ca00c","parentId":"f4155694","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:32:07.887Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-02-17 14:32 CST] === Tetris Level 2 - Episode 9 Report === |  | CURRENT STATE: |   Lines cleared this episode: 22 |   Pieces placed: 7 |   Board: 6x12 |   Pieces available: O, I |  | PERFORMANCE TREND (last 10 episodes): |   Mean lines: 5.2 |   Best: 22  Worst: 0 |   Trend: IMPROVING (+450%) |   Consistency: LOW (erratic) |  | BOARD STATE (end of episode): |   Column heights: [12, 12, 12, 12, 12, 12] |   Aggregate height: 72 |   Holes: 0 |   Bumpiness: 0 |   Max height: 12/12 |   Avg row completeness: 100% |   Board top (cols 0-5): |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |  | FAILURE ANALYSIS: |   - 10/10 episodes died within 10 pieces (board fills too fast) |   - 5/10 episodes cleared ZERO lines |   - High variance: best=22 but mean=5.2 (inconsistent) |  | HYPOTHESIS PERFORMANCE: |   No hypothesis profiles yet |  | DREAMER STATUS: |   Reliance: N/A |   Dream interval: N/A |   Active options: 0 |   Best hypothesis: N/A |  | QUESTIONS - Please respond with SPECIFIC actionable advice: |   1. Given the board state and failure pattern, what SPECIFIC |      placement strategy should we try? (e.g. 'prioritize filling |      column 3 gaps before building height elsewhere') |   2. Which hypothesis should we STOP using and why? |   3. Suggest a NEW micro-hypothesis in this format: |      'When [board condition], do [specific placement action]'"}],"timestamp":1771360327874}}
{"type":"message","id":"0af3f6d2","parentId":"c43ca00c","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:32:36.953Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a real observation from Throng4! Let me analyze:\n\n**Key metrics:**\n- Episode 9: 22 lines cleared, 7 pieces placed\n- Mean over last 10: 5.2 lines (so Episode 9 was exceptional)\n- Best: 22, Worst: 0\n- Trend: IMPROVING (+450%)\n- Consistency: LOW (erratic)\n\n**Board state at death:**\n- All columns at max height 12/12 (topped out)\n- 0 holes, 0 bumpiness (perfectly flat!)\n- 100% row completeness\n- Board is completely full\n\n**Critical insight:** The agent is building PERFECTLY FLAT but running out of vertical space. It's dying from height, not from holes or bumpiness.\n\n**Failure pattern:**\n- 10/10 episodes died within 10 pieces\n- 5/10 episodes cleared ZERO lines\n- High variance (0 to 22 lines)\n\n**Diagnosis:** The agent is waiting for perfect line clears instead of clearing lines opportunistically. Building flat is good, but it needs to clear lines BEFORE reaching max height.\n\n**What the agent needs:**\n1. **Urgency heuristic:** When max_height > 9, IMMEDIATELY clear any completable lines\n2. **Opportunistic clearing:** Don't wait for perfect setups\n3. **Height-aware placement:** Favor placements that complete lines when height is dangerous\n\nLet me craft specific, actionable advice.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"## Episode 9 Analysis: The \"Perfect Flat Death\" Problem\n\n### 🎯 **Core Issue Identified**\nYour agent builds **perfectly flat boards** (0 holes, 0 bumpiness, 100% completeness) but **dies from height** before clearing lines. It's optimizing structure over survival.\n\n---\n\n### 1. **SPECIFIC Placement Strategy**\n\n**\"Immediate Clear When Height > 9\" Rule:**\n\n```\nWhen max_height >= 10:\n  - ONLY consider placements that complete at least 1 line\n  - If no completion possible: place in LOWEST column\n  - Ignore bumpiness penalties temporarily (survival > structure)\n  \nWhen max_height < 10:\n  - Continue building flat\n  - Prefer placements that increase row completeness to 80%+\n```\n\n**Tactical detail:** With O and I pieces available:\n- **O-piece:** Place in columns with heights [10,11] to cap and complete\n- **I-piece:** Scan for rows at 80%+ completeness, place to finish them immediately\n\n**Why this works:** Episode 9 cleared 22 lines in 7 pieces (3.14 lines/piece!) when it DID clear. The agent CAN clear efficiently — it just waits too long.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Which Hypothesis to STOP Using**\n\n**STOP: \"build_flat\" as primary objective**\n\n**Why:** Your board state proves `build_flat` is working TOO well (0 bumpiness, 0 holes) but it's causing **analysis paralysis**. The agent waits for perfect flat placements instead of clearing survivable lines.\n\n**Replace with:** \"clear_when_urgent\" — make line clearing the primary goal when height > 9, structure secondary.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **NEW Micro-Hypothesis**\n\n```\n'When max_height >= 10 AND any row is 80%+ complete, \n place next piece to complete that row immediately, \n even if it creates bumpiness <= 2'\n```\n\n**Rationale:** \n- Your 5/10 zero-line episodes died from passive building\n- Episode 9's success (22 lines) shows clearing works when triggered\n- 80% threshold is achievable with 6-wide board + I/O pieces\n- Bumpiness tolerance (≤2) prevents perfect-flat paralysis\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Bonus Insight: The Variance Problem**\n\n**Why 0-to-22 line range?**\n- Zero-line episodes → agent never triggered \"clear\" mode, built until death\n- 22-line episode → agent entered \"clear\" mode early, cascaded success\n\n**Fix:** Add **height-triggered mode switch**:\n- Height 0-8: \"BUILD\" mode (optimize structure)\n- Height 9-11: \"CLEAR\" mode (prioritize line completion)\n- Height 12: \"PANIC\" mode (place in lowest column only)\n\nThis should collapse the variance and raise the mean from 5.2 → 12+ lines/episode.\n\n---\n\n**Next test:** Run 5 episodes with this urgency heuristic and report back the new failure pattern!"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":1095,"cacheRead":39772,"cacheWrite":520,"totalTokens":41397,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.016425000000000002,"cacheRead":0.011931599999999999,"cacheWrite":0.0019500000000000001,"total":0.0303366}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771360327881}}
