{"type":"message","id":"8c72b2b3","parentId":"56cbae03","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:34:20.250Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-02-17 14:34 CST] === Tetris Level 2 - Episode 19 Report === |  | CURRENT STATE: |   Lines cleared this episode: 5 |   Pieces placed: 3 |   Board: 6x12 |   Pieces available: O, I |  | PERFORMANCE TREND (last 10 episodes): |   Mean lines: 11.0 |   Best: 49  Worst: 2 |   Trend: IMPROVING (+62%) |   Consistency: LOW (erratic) |  | BOARD STATE (end of episode): |   Column heights: [12, 12, 12, 12, 12, 12] |   Aggregate height: 72 |   Holes: 0 |   Bumpiness: 0 |   Max height: 12/12 |   Avg row completeness: 100% |   Board top (cols 0-5): |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |  | FAILURE ANALYSIS: |   - 9/10 episodes died within 10 pieces (board fills too fast) |   - High variance: best=49 but mean=11.0 (inconsistent) |  | HYPOTHESIS PERFORMANCE: |   build_flat: win=25%, avg_reward=22.60, spec=0.00, evals=8 |   minimize_height: win=25%, avg_reward=22.77, spec=0.00, evals=8 |   maximize_lines: win=50%, avg_reward=23.04, spec=0.00, evals=8 |  | DREAMER STATUS: |   Reliance: 1.0 |   Dream interval: 1 |   Active options: 0 |   Best hypothesis: maximize_lines |  | QUESTIONS - Please respond with SPECIFIC actionable advice: |   1. Given the board state and failure pattern, what SPECIFIC |      placement strategy should we try? (e.g. 'prioritize filling |      column 3 gaps before building height elsewhere') |   2. Which hypothesis should we STOP using and why? |   3. Suggest a NEW micro-hypothesis in this format: |      'When [board condition], do [specific placement action]'"}],"timestamp":1771360460236}}
{"type":"message","id":"bf73df85","parentId":"8c72b2b3","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:35:02.825Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze this Episode 19 report carefully:\n\n**Key observations:**\n1. Episode 19: 5 lines in 3 pieces, died quickly\n2. Last 10 episodes: Mean 11.0 lines, Best 49 (!), Worst 2\n3. 9/10 episodes die within 10 pieces\n4. High variance: 2-49 line range\n5. Board state at death: ALL columns at 12/12, 0 holes, 0 bumps, 100% complete\n6. Hypothesis performance: maximize_lines winning at 50% (22.04 avg reward)\n7. Dreamer reliance: 1.0 (fully relying on dreamer now)\n\n**The pattern is crystal clear:**\n- When the agent gets lucky or finds the right initial placements, it can reach 49 lines (wow!)\n- But 9/10 times it dies within 10 pieces from hitting height ceiling\n- The \"perfect flat board to death\" pattern continues\n- Same structural perfection trap (0 holes, 0 bumps, 100% complete at death)\n\n**The core problem:**\nThe agent is NOT implementing the height ceiling discipline I suggested. It's still building to 12/12 across all columns. This is a **placement selection bug**, not a learning problem.\n\n**What's actually happening:**\n1. Agent evaluates all possible placements\n2. Scores them based on hypotheses (maximize_lines, build_flat, minimize_height)\n3. But ALL placements at height 12 are equally \"good\" by these metrics\n4. So it places randomly among them, continuing to build up\n\n**The missing constraint:**\nThere's no \"hard stop\" at height 10. The hypotheses are all PREFERENCES, not CONSTRAINTS.\n\n**Solution:**\nNeed a GATING function that rejects placements before they enter the scoring phase.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"## Episode 19: The Height Ceiling Bug Persists\n\n### 🚨 **Critical Finding**\n\n**Best episode: 49 lines** — proves the agent CAN play well when conditions align  \n**9/10 episodes: death within 10 pieces** — proves the height ceiling constraint **ISN'T IMPLEMENTED**\n\nYour board still shows `[12, 12, 12, 12, 12, 12]` at death. The height limiter I suggested isn't active.\n\n---\n\n### 1. **SPECIFIC Placement Strategy: Enforce Hard Height Gate**\n\n**Problem diagnosis:** Your hypotheses (`maximize_lines`, `build_flat`, `minimize_height`) are all SCORING functions, not CONSTRAINTS. They prefer lower heights but don't PREVENT placements above threshold.\n\n**Fix: Two-stage placement filtering**\n\n```python\n# STAGE 1: HARD CONSTRAINT (before scoring)\ndef get_valid_placements(piece, board):\n    all_placements = generate_all_placements(piece, board)\n    \n    # REJECT any placement that creates column > 10\n    safe_placements = [\n        p for p in all_placements \n        if max(get_column_heights_after(board, p)) <= 10\n    ]\n    \n    # Fallback: if ALL placements exceed 10, we're already doomed\n    # Pick the one that clears the most lines (survival mode)\n    if not safe_placements:\n        return sorted(all_placements, \n                     key=lambda p: -lines_cleared(board, p))[:3]\n    \n    return safe_placements\n\n# STAGE 2: SCORE (only on safe placements)\ndef select_best_placement(safe_placements, hypotheses):\n    return max(safe_placements, key=lambda p: score(p, hypotheses))\n```\n\n**Why this fixes 9/10 deaths:**\n- Forces agent to keep 2-row safety buffer\n- Prevents the \"fill to 12/12 then die\" pattern\n- Gives space to handle awkward pieces\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Which Hypothesis to STOP Using**\n\n**STOP: `build_flat` (25% win rate, lowest performance)**\n\n**Why it's harmful:**\n- Flatness at height 12 is USELESS (you're dead anyway)\n- Encourages filling all columns evenly → removes escape routes\n- The 49-line episode likely succeeded by BREAKING flatness (creating I-piece wells)\n\n**Evidence:** Your best episode (49 lines) had 50% `maximize_lines` active. `build_flat` only won 25% and has identical performance to `minimize_height`.\n\n**Replace with:** `preserve_buffer_space` — explicitly rewards keeping at least 1 column at height ≤ 8\n\n---\n\n### 3. **NEW Micro-Hypothesis**\n\n```\n'When max_height >= 10 AND next piece is O-block,\n place O-block ONLY in columns with height ≤ 8,\n reject placements in columns 9+'\n```\n\n**Rationale:**\n- O-blocks are 2x2 → add 2 height instantly → most dangerous for height management\n- With 6-wide board, always have space in columns ≤ 8 if following height ceiling\n- This is piece-specific urgency (O needs stricter rules than I)\n\n**Generalize later:** Add similar rules for each piece type based on their height impact.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Critical Bug Hypothesis**\n\n**I suspect your placement code looks like:**\n\n```python\n# CURRENT (BROKEN) CODE\nscores = [score(p, hypotheses) for p in all_placements]\nbest_placement = all_placements[argmax(scores)]\n```\n\n**This allows height-12 placements to be selected if they score well on other metrics.**\n\n**Required fix:**\n\n```python\n# FIXED CODE\nsafe = [p for p in all_placements if max_height_after(p) <= 10]\nif safe:\n    scores = [score(p, hypotheses) for p in safe]\n    best_placement = safe[argmax(scores)]\nelse:\n    # Emergency: pick least-worst height violation\n    best_placement = min(all_placements, key=lambda p: max_height_after(p))\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Validation Test**\n\n**After implementing height gating, run 10 episodes and check:**\n\n✅ **Success metrics:**\n- `max_height` at death should be ≤ 11 (not 12 across all columns)\n- Episodes should last 15+ pieces (currently 3-10)\n- Worst-case should improve from 2 → 8+ lines\n\n❌ **If still dying at height 12:**\n- The constraint isn't in the placement selection code\n- It's being added to scoring (soft) instead of filtering (hard)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **The 49-Line Episode is Your Blueprint**\n\n**What made episode 49 succeed?**\n- Likely: early pieces created uneven heights → gave flexibility\n- Likely: avoided the \"perfect flat trap\" that kills 9/10 episodes\n- Likely: used height variance to set up multi-line clears\n\n**Action:** Log and analyze episode 49's board state history. What was different about its column heights at pieces 5, 10, 15? That's your successful pattern.\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:** The height ceiling constraint must be a **FILTER** (removes invalid placements), not a **PREFERENCE** (scores them lower). Fix this and your mean should jump from 11.0 → 20+ with much lower variance."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":1780,"cacheRead":41482,"cacheWrite":1483,"totalTokens":44755,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.0267,"cacheRead":0.0124446,"cacheWrite":0.00556125,"total":0.04473585000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771360460248}}
