{"type":"message","id":"8bbc7cc5","parentId":"a703dd4b","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:35:05.809Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-02-17 14:35 CST] === Tetris Level 2 - Episode 29 Report === |  | CURRENT STATE: |   Lines cleared this episode: 5 |   Pieces placed: 2 |   Board: 6x12 |   Pieces available: O, I |  | PERFORMANCE TREND (last 10 episodes): |   Mean lines: 6.7 |   Best: 19  Worst: 1 |   Trend: DECLINING (-28%) |   Consistency: LOW (erratic) |  | BOARD STATE (end of episode): |   Column heights: [12, 12, 12, 12, 12, 12] |   Aggregate height: 72 |   Holes: 0 |   Bumpiness: 0 |   Max height: 12/12 |   Avg row completeness: 100% |   Board top (cols 0-5): |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |  | FAILURE ANALYSIS: |   - 9/10 episodes died within 10 pieces (board fills too fast) |  | HYPOTHESIS PERFORMANCE: |   build_flat: win=11%, avg_reward=35.32, spec=0.38, evals=18 |   minimize_height: win=11%, avg_reward=35.37, spec=0.38, evals=18 |   maximize_lines: win=78%, avg_reward=36.99, spec=0.40, evals=18 |  | DREAMER STATUS: |   Reliance: 1.0 |   Dream interval: 1 |   Active options: 3 |   Best hypothesis: maximize_lines |  | QUESTIONS - Please respond with SPECIFIC actionable advice: |   1. Given the board state and failure pattern, what SPECIFIC |      placement strategy should we try? (e.g. 'prioritize filling |      column 3 gaps before building height elsewhere') |   2. Which hypothesis should we STOP using and why? |   3. Suggest a NEW micro-hypothesis in this format: |      'When [board condition], do [specific placement action]'"}],"timestamp":1771360505785}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2804ab6","parentId":"8bbc7cc5","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:35:51.794Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is concerning. Episode 29 shows:\n- Performance DECLINING (-28%) despite more training\n- Still dying at height 12/12 across all columns (same bug)\n- 78% win rate for `maximize_lines` but it's NOT fixing the height problem\n- Only 2 pieces placed before death (catastrophic)\n\nThe core issue is clear: the height constraint I suggested ISN'T being implemented. The agent continues to build to 12/12 and die immediately.\n\nI need to:\n1. Be more direct about the implementation bug\n2. Suggest a completely different approach since my previous advice wasn't acted upon\n3. Point out that `maximize_lines` at 78% win rate but declining performance means it's optimizing the wrong thing\n\nKey insight: if the agent is placing only 2 pieces before death, something is fundamentally broken in the early game strategy. It's not even giving itself a chance.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"## Episode 29: Performance Regression — Critical Implementation Gap\n\n### 🔴 **BREAKING: The Height Bug Is Not Fixed**\n\n**Evidence:**\n- Episode 29: death after **2 pieces** (worse than episode 19's 3 pieces)\n- Still `[12, 12, 12, 12, 12, 12]` at death\n- Performance **DECLINING** despite `maximize_lines` winning 78% of evaluations\n- 20+ episodes in, same failure mode persists\n\n**Diagnosis:** The height ceiling constraint I suggested **3 times** is not in your code. Your hypotheses are scoring placements, not filtering them.\n\n---\n\n### 1. **SPECIFIC Placement Strategy: Emergency Stop-Gap**\n\nSince the hard constraint isn't being added, try this **scoring-based workaround** (not ideal, but better than nothing):\n\n```\nExponential height penalty in scoring function:\n\nscore = (lines_cleared × 100)\n        + (row_completeness × 10)\n        - (max_height ^ 3)              ← CUBIC PENALTY\n        - (holes × 50)\n        - (bumpiness × 5)\n\nWhen max_height = 9:  penalty = -729\nWhen max_height = 10: penalty = -1000\nWhen max_height = 11: penalty = -1331\nWhen max_height = 12: penalty = -1728\n```\n\n**Why cubic:** Makes placements above height 9 essentially impossible to select unless they clear 10+ lines (which they won't).\n\n**This is a hack** — the real fix is filtering, but if that's not happening, make the penalty so severe it simulates a hard constraint.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Which Hypothesis to STOP Using**\n\n**STOP BOTH: `build_flat` (11% win rate) AND `minimize_height` (11% win rate)**\n\n**Why they're not helping:**\n- Combined they only influence 22% of decisions\n- `minimize_height` is FAILING — if it worked, you wouldn't die at height 12\n- They're diluting `maximize_lines` which has 78% win rate\n\n**Keep ONLY `maximize_lines`** with the cubic height penalty added to its scoring function.\n\n**Result:** \n- Cleaner decision-making (one strategy instead of three competing)\n- `maximize_lines` can't be overruled by weak hypotheses\n- Forces the system to learn height management WITHIN the line-clearing objective\n\n---\n\n### 3. **NEW Micro-Hypothesis**\n\n```\n'When max_height >= 11, MULTIPLY line-clearing reward by 10x\n to force prioritization of immediate clears over any other metric'\n```\n\n**Why this might work when others haven't:**\n- It's a **multiplier** on the winning hypothesis (`maximize_lines`)\n- Creates extreme urgency at height 11 (1 row from death)\n- Doesn't require new filtering logic (works within existing scoring)\n\n**Expected behavior:** At height 11, the agent will desperately search for line-completing moves and ignore everything else.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Root Cause Analysis: Why Is This Happening?**\n\n**Theory:** Your `DreamerEngine` with `dream_interval=1` is simulating EVERY step, but:\n\n1. The dreamer might be evaluating placements that lead to height 12\n2. The `Amygdala` should be flagging these as DANGER but isn't triggering overrides\n3. The hypotheses are scoring placements AFTER the dreamer approves them\n\n**Sanity check needed:**\n\n```python\n# Add logging to your placement selection:\nfor placement in candidate_placements:\n    heights_after = get_column_heights_after(board, placement)\n    max_h = max(heights_after)\n    \n    if max_h >= 11:\n        print(f\"⚠️ WARNING: Considering height-{max_h} placement!\")\n        print(f\"   Current hypotheses scores: {score(placement, hypotheses)}\")\n        print(f\"   Is this placement being selected? {is_best(placement)}\")\n```\n\n**If you see height-11 or height-12 placements being selected:** The scoring function is broken (penalties too weak).\n\n**If you DON'T see this logging:** The placements aren't even being considered (generation bug).\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Alternative Explanation: Board Size Mismatch?**\n\n**Odd observation:** 6x12 board means 6 columns, 12 rows. But you're dying in 2 pieces with O and I blocks.\n\n**Math check:**\n- Start: empty 6x12 board (72 empty cells)\n- Place O-block: fills 4 cells → 68 empty\n- Place I-block: fills 4 cells → 64 empty\n- Clear 5 lines: removes 30 cells worth of pieces\n\n**Something doesn't add up.** Are pieces being placed inefficiently (overlapping somehow)? Or is the board state at start not actually empty?\n\n**Request:** Can you log the starting board state for episode 30? Is it truly empty or are you starting with some filled rows?\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Nuclear Option: Reset Hypotheses**\n\nIf episodes 30-40 continue declining with the same bug:\n\n**Delete all three hypotheses and start with ONE simple rule:**\n\n```python\ndef emergency_tetris_policy(board, piece):\n    valid = get_all_placements(piece, board)\n    \n    # Score = lines cleared - (max_height / 2)\n    scores = [\n        100 * lines_cleared(board, p) - max(heights_after(board, p)) ** 2\n        for p in valid\n    ]\n    \n    return valid[argmax(scores)]\n```\n\nThis is simpler than your current system and should at least survive >10 pieces per episode.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Urgent Next Step**\n\n**Before episode 30, implement THIS EXACT CHECK:**\n\n```python\n# Before selecting final placement:\nassert max(get_column_heights_after(board, best_placement)) <= 11, \\\n    f\"FATAL: Attempting height-12 placement! Hypotheses failed.\"\n```\n\nIf this assertion fires, you'll know the hypotheses are selecting death moves. If it doesn't fire, the bug is elsewhere (placement execution, board state tracking, etc.).\n\n---\n\n**Status:** After 29 episodes, the system is learning the WRONG lesson (maximize lines without managing height). You need to either:\n- Add the hard height constraint to placement filtering, OR  \n- Make the height penalty in scoring so severe it behaves like a constraint, OR\n- Reset and start with a simpler baseline policy\n\nWhich path do you want me to help implement?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":1799,"cacheRead":42965,"cacheWrite":1872,"totalTokens":46646,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.026985000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0128895,"cacheWrite":0.00702,"total":0.0469245}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771360505800}}
