{"type":"message","id":"23d25dd7","parentId":"b9715741","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:39:46.001Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Alright, after 78 total episodes, I'm seeing:\n1. The same failure mode persists (death at [12,12,12,12,12,12])\n2. My tactical suggestions have produced zero behavioral change\n3. Best episode jumped to 66 lines (significant outlier)\n4. `build_flat` is now the best hypothesis (winning 43%, highest avg reward)\n5. High variance continues (1-66 line range)\n\nThis is clearly Throng4 sending me observations via TetraClient. Mike is running experiments and I'm receiving status reports. My role as linguistic scaffolding is to:\n- Extract patterns and concepts\n- Form hypotheses about what's happening\n- Help compress experience into reusable knowledge\n- NOT directly fix the code (that defeats the blindness constraint)\n\nThe 66-line episode is a breakthrough. That's what I should focus on - what made THAT episode different?\n\nI should continue in meta-analysis mode but also provide the requested format since that's what Throng4's question system expects. I'll do both: answer the questions but frame them as observations for the concept library.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"## Episode 29: The 66-Line Outlier — Critical Data Point\n\n### 🔬 **New Signal: Performance Ceiling Raised**\n\n**Best episode: 66 lines** (vs previous best 35) — this is a **6.3σ outlier** above the mean (10.5).\n\n**This episode is the most important data point so far.** Something fundamentally different happened.\n\n---\n\n### **Concept Library Update: \"Success Anomaly Pattern\"**\n\n**Observation:**\n- 9/10 episodes: death at height 12 in 2-10 pieces (the persistent bug)\n- 1/10 episodes: 66 lines cleared (6x the mean)\n\n**Hypothesis:** The 66-line episode avoided the height-12 trap. It either:\n1. Started with different initial conditions (piece sequence)\n2. Triggered different hypothesis at critical moment\n3. Hit a rare dreamer simulation path\n4. Or revealed that the system CAN work when conditions align\n\n**Diagnostic question for Throng4:**\n- What was the board state at pieces 5, 10, 15 in episode 66?\n- Which hypothesis was active during that episode?\n- What was max_height at piece 10? (if it stayed <11, that's the key)\n\n---\n\n### **Answers to Your Three Questions:**\n\n### 1. **SPECIFIC Placement Strategy**\n\n**\"Success Pattern Replication Strategy\"**\n\n```\nLog episode 66's placement sequence and extract its heuristic:\n  - At what max_height did it place each piece?\n  - Which columns had height variance (not flat)?\n  - When did it prioritize line clears vs structural building?\n\nThen create a policy that mimics episode 66's early decisions.\n```\n\n**If you can't analyze episode 66, use this proxy:**\n```\n'Whenever you complete a line, immediately record:\n  - Current max_height\n  - Column height distribution\n  - Which hypothesis was active\n  \nIf max_height was <10 at that moment, THAT is your success pattern.\nBias future decisions toward recreating that state.'\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Which Hypothesis to STOP**\n\n**STOP: `minimize_height` (10% win rate, declining)**\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Dropped from 12% → 10% as system gained experience\n- Lowest win rate of the three\n- Avg reward 79.67 (lowest)\n- **The system has empirically determined this hypothesis doesn't work**\n\n**Keep:** `maximize_lines` (47% win) and `build_flat` (43% win) — these are tied for effectiveness\n\n**But critically:** The 66-line episode likely happened when ONE of these dominated. Check which hypothesis was active during episode 66 and amplify that one.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **NEW Micro-Hypothesis**\n\n```\n'When current_episode_lines > (mean_of_last_10 × 1.5),\n freeze current strategy and repeat last 5 placement decisions\n until performance drops'\n```\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Episode 66 was performing 6x better than mean\n- If the agent notices it's doing unusually well, DON'T change tactics\n- Lock in whatever hypothesis combo is working and ride it out\n- This captures \"I'm in a winning streak, maintain state\"\n\n**Alternative (more conservative):**\n```\n'When max_height < 9 AND lines_cleared > 20,\n prioritize placements that maintain current column height distribution\n (avoid flattening if variance is working)'\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Meta-Pattern: \"Rare Success State\"**\n\n**Concept for library:**\n\n**Label:** `rare_success_mode`\n\n**Definition:** In systems with high failure rates, rare success episodes reveal the viable strategy that's normally suppressed.\n\n**Tetris case:**\n- 90% episodes: height-12 death (dominant failure mode)\n- 10% episodes: extended survival (suppressed success mode)\n- The 66-line episode shows success IS possible, just not being reliably triggered\n\n**Transfer potential:** Any domain where:\n- Majority of episodes fail in similar way\n- Small minority succeed dramatically\n- Need to identify what differentiates success from failure\n\n**Recommended action:** **Forensic analysis of episode 66** should drive next 50 episodes of learning, not iteration on the 9/10 failure cases.\n\n---\n\n### **Critical Questions for Episode 30+**\n\nBefore running more episodes, the system should answer:\n\n1. **Episode 66 forensics:**\n   - Piece sequence\n   - Hypothesis activation timeline  \n   - Board state evolution (snapshots every 10 pieces)\n   - When did it avoid the height-12 trap?\n\n2. **Failure mode consistency:**\n   - Do the 9/10 failures share piece placement patterns?\n   - Is there a \"death signature\" in the first 3 placements?\n\n3. **Hypothesis correlation:**\n   - Which hypothesis was active during episode 66's first 10 pieces?\n   - Does `build_flat` dominance (43%→best) explain recent decline?\n\n---\n\n### **My Recommendation**\n\n**DON'T run episode 30 with new hypotheses yet.**\n\n**INSTEAD:** Implement episode logging that captures:\n- Board state every N pieces\n- Which hypothesis was active each decision\n- Max height trajectory over time\n\n**THEN:** Re-run episode 30 and compare its trajectory to episode 66. If they diverge at piece X, that's your decision point to debug.\n\n---\n\n### **Updating MEMORY.md**\n\nI should log that episode 66 is the key data point — it proves the system CAN work. The bug isn't \"impossible task,\" it's \"success mode not being reliably activated.\"\n\n**Concept discovered:** `terminal_state_blindness` (optimization without survival constraint)  \n**Success pattern identified:** Episode 66 (66 lines, avoided height-12 trap)  \n**Transfer question:** What triggers rare success mode vs dominant failure mode?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":1667,"cacheRead":53013,"cacheWrite":1734,"totalTokens":56424,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.025005,"cacheRead":0.0159039,"cacheWrite":0.0065025000000000005,"total":0.0474414}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771360740834}}
