{"type":"message","id":"72526fb6","parentId":"410ad5e8","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:42:34.491Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-02-17 14:42 CST] === Tetris Level 3 - Episode 69 Report === |  | CURRENT STATE: |   Lines cleared this episode: 9 |   Pieces placed: 3 |   Board: 6x12 |   Pieces available: O, I, T |  | PERFORMANCE TREND (last 10 episodes): |   Mean lines: 14.4 |   Best: 42  Worst: 1 |   Trend: IMPROVING (+82%) |   Consistency: LOW (erratic) |  | BOARD STATE (end of episode): |   Column heights: [12, 12, 12, 12, 12, 12] |   Aggregate height: 72 |   Holes: 0 |   Bumpiness: 0 |   Max height: 12/12 |   Avg row completeness: 100% |   Board top (cols 0-5): |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |   |######| |  | FAILURE ANALYSIS: |   - 7/10 episodes died within 10 pieces (board fills too fast) |  | HYPOTHESIS PERFORMANCE: |   build_flat: win=36%, avg_reward=113.46, spec=0.48, evals=108 |   minimize_height: win=16%, avg_reward=113.01, spec=0.49, evals=108 |   maximize_lines: win=48%, avg_reward=115.22, spec=0.49, evals=108 |  | DREAMER STATUS: |   Reliance: 1.0 |   Dream interval: 1 |   Active options: 3 |   Best hypothesis: maximize_lines |  | QUESTIONS - Please respond with SPECIFIC actionable advice: |   1. Given the board state and failure pattern, what SPECIFIC |      placement strategy should we try? (e.g. 'prioritize filling |      column 3 gaps before building height elsewhere') |   2. Which hypothesis should we STOP using and why? |   3. Suggest a NEW micro-hypothesis in this format: |      'When [board condition], do [specific placement action]'"}],"timestamp":1771360954477}}
{"type":"message","id":"f132317b","parentId":"72526fb6","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:43:23.127Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is interesting - Episode 69 shows a REGRESSION:\n- Episode 59: Mean 22.3\n- Episode 69: Mean 14.4\n\nThat's a -35% decline. My prediction was mean would be 27-28, but it's actually 14.4.\n\nWhat changed?\n- maximize_lines increased: 43% → 48% (good)\n- build_flat decreased: 40% → 36% (expected)\n- minimize_height stable: 17% → 16%\n\nBut performance got WORSE despite maximize_lines winning more often.\n\nThis is a critical data point. Either:\n1. The system hit a local maximum and is now exploring (normal in learning)\n2. Something changed in the environment or reward structure\n3. The learning is unstable (oscillating)\n4. My analysis was wrong about what was driving improvement\n\nThe variance also increased (best dropped from 49 to 42).\n\nI should acknowledge the prediction failure and diagnose what happened.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"## Episode 69: Regression — Prediction Failed\n\n### ⚠️ **Unexpected Performance Decline**\n\n**My prediction for Episode 69:** Mean 27-28 lines  \n**Actual Episode 69:** Mean 14.4 lines  \n**Error:** -47% (massive miss)\n\n**This is a critical learning moment for me (Tetra).** My pattern recognition was wrong, or something changed.\n\n---\n\n### **What Happened Between Episode 59 → 69?**\n\n**Performance trajectory:**\n```\nEpisode 49: Mean 17.9, improving\nEpisode 59: Mean 22.3, peak ← I predicted continuation\nEpisode 69: Mean 14.4, crashed ← Reality\n```\n\n**Hypothesis shift:**\n- `maximize_lines`: 43% → 48% (increased dominance)\n- `build_flat`: 40% → 36% (decreased as predicted)\n- `minimize_height`: 17% → 16% (stable)\n\n**Contradiction:** The \"best\" hypothesis (`maximize_lines`) increased control, but performance got worse.\n\n---\n\n### **Diagnostic Hypotheses**\n\n**A) Overfitting to maximize_lines:**\n- At 48% dominance, `maximize_lines` might be too aggressive\n- Sacrifices board structure for immediate clears\n- Creates unstable states that collapse quickly\n\n**B) Exploration spike:**\n- Learning algorithms often regress temporarily when exploring\n- Episode 59-69 might have higher epsilon (exploration rate)\n- Would explain: 7/10 quick deaths, erratic behavior\n\n**C) Reward signal changed:**\n- Avg reward still increasing (113→115), but mean performance declined\n- Suggests: Reward and actual performance are decoupling\n- System optimizing the wrong metric\n\n**D) Stochastic variance:**\n- Just bad luck in piece sequences for episodes 60-69\n- But 10-episode window should smooth this out\n- Less likely, but possible\n\n**E) Cascade equilibrium broke:**\n- System pushed line-clearing rate too high\n- Created structural instability (holes, bad placements)\n- Temporary success followed by rapid collapse\n\n---\n\n### **Updating My Mental Model**\n\n**What I got wrong:**\n- Assumed linear improvement would continue\n- Didn't account for learning instability\n- Predicted based on 10-episode trend without considering oscillation\n\n**What I should have predicted:**\n- Learning curves oscillate (explore/exploit cycles)\n- Local maxima followed by dips are normal\n- Need 20-30 episode windows for stable trends\n\n**Revised understanding:**\n- Episode 49-59 was exploitation phase (refining known pattern)\n- Episode 60-69 might be exploration phase (testing boundaries)\n- Expect re-convergence in episodes 70-80\n\n---\n\n### **Answers to Questions**\n\n### 1. **Placement Strategy**\n\n**\"Reduce maximize_lines dominance\"**\n\nAt 48% win rate, `maximize_lines` might be over-optimizing for immediate clearing at expense of stability.\n\n**Specific strategy:**\n```\nRebalance hypothesis weights:\n  maximize_lines: 48% → 40% (reduce by 17%)\n  build_flat: 36% → 45% (increase by 25%)\n  minimize_height: 16% → 15% (keep stable)\n\nGoal: Restore structural discipline while maintaining clearing efficiency\n```\n\n**Test:** If episodes 70-79 mean rises back above 18, this confirms `maximize_lines` overfit.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Hypothesis to STOP**\n\n**STOP: minimize_height (16% win rate, no improvement)**\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Stuck at 16-17% for 30+ episodes\n- Lowest avg reward consistently\n- No specialization emerging (spec 0.49, same as others)\n- Freeing this capacity might stabilize the other two\n\n**Reallocate:**\n- `maximize_lines`: 40% total (reduced from current 48%)\n- `build_flat`: 60% total (increased significantly)\n\n**Hypothesis:** The regression was caused by too much line-clearing aggression. Shifting weight to structural stability might restore episode 59 performance.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **NEW Micro-Hypothesis**\n\n```\n'When lines_cleared / pieces_placed > 3.0,\n SLOW DOWN: prioritize placements that reduce bumpiness and holes,\n accept 0-line placements for next 2 pieces to stabilize board'\n```\n\n**Rationale:**\n- Detects when clearing rate is unsustainably high\n- Forces a stabilization pause before collapse\n- Targets the \"cascade broke\" failure mode\n\n**Alternative (more conservative):**\n```\n'When max_height >= 9 AND holes > 0,\n enter REPAIR mode: prioritize filling holes over clearing lines\n until holes = 0, then resume normal strategy'\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Meta-Analysis: What This Teaches Me**\n\n**Concept discovered:** `\"optimization_oscillation\"`\n\n**Definition:**  \nIn autonomous learning systems, performance oscillates as the system explores boundaries. Local maxima are followed by temporary regressions before reconvergence at (hopefully) higher global maximum.\n\n**Pattern signature:**\n- Phase 1: Improvement (episode 40-59)\n- Phase 2: Regression (episode 60-69)\n- Phase 3: Reconvergence (episode 70-80, predicted)\n\n**Tetris manifestation:**\n- System learned efficient clearing (episode 59 peak)\n- Pushed too far, sacrificed stability (episode 69 crash)\n- Should learn balanced strategy (episode 80, predicted)\n\n**Transfer pattern:**  \nAny optimization where multiple objectives compete (efficiency vs stability, speed vs accuracy, reward vs risk).\n\n**Lesson for me:**\nDon't extrapolate linear trends. Learning is cyclical. Need longer observation windows for prediction.\n\n---\n\n### **Revised Prediction for Episode 79**\n\n**IF regression was exploration:**\n- Mean: 19-21 lines (recovery toward episode 59 level)\n- `build_flat` should increase above 40%\n- Variance should decrease slightly\n\n**IF regression was structural (overfitting):**\n- Mean: stays at 14-16 lines (stuck)\n- Need to remove `minimize_height` and rebalance\n- Consider adding bootstrap hypothesis\n\n**Validation metric:** Episode 79 mean relative to episode 69\n- >18 lines = exploration recovery\n- <16 lines = structural problem needs intervention\n\n---\n\n### **Memory Update: Learning Curves Are Not Linear**\n\n**Episode 69 milestone:**\n- Unexpected regression: 22.3 → 14.4 mean\n- `maximize_lines` dominance increased despite performance decline\n- Possible overfitting or exploration phase\n- **My prediction was wrong** — need longer observation windows\n\n**Lessons learned (for me):**\n1. Short-term trends (10 episodes) can mislead\n2. Oscillation is normal in learning systems\n3. Correlation (hypothesis win rate) ≠ causation (performance)\n4. Need 20-30 episode windows for stable predictions\n\n**Concept library update:**\n- `optimization_oscillation` — explore/exploit cycles cause performance waves\n- `hypothesis_overfit` — dominant strategy can become too aggressive\n\n**Next observation point:** Episode 79 to test recovery hypothesis\n\n---\n\n**TL;DR:** I was overconfident in the trend. Learning regressed, possibly because `maximize_lines` overfitted. Recommendation: Reduce its weight, increase `build_flat`, remove `minimize_height`. Watch episode 70-79 to see if this recovers performance or if deeper intervention is needed."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":2022,"cacheRead":60878,"cacheWrite":2360,"totalTokens":65270,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.03033,"cacheRead":0.0182634,"cacheWrite":0.00885,"total":0.057473399999999994}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771360954488}}
