{"type":"message","id":"a99c6844","parentId":"2ec56190","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:48:46.707Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-02-17 14:48 CST] === Tetris Level 4 - Episode 19 Report === |  | CURRENT STATE: |   Lines cleared this episode: 1 |   Pieces placed: 2 |   Board: 8x14 |   Pieces available: O, I, T, S, Z |  | PERFORMANCE TREND (last 10 episodes): |   Mean lines: 4.9 |   Best: 19  Worst: 1 |   Trend: IMPROVING (+58%) |   Consistency: LOW (erratic) |  | BOARD STATE (end of episode): |   Column heights: [14, 14, 14, 14, 14, 14, 14, 14] |   Aggregate height: 112 |   Holes: 0 |   Bumpiness: 0 |   Max height: 14/14 |   Avg row completeness: 100% |   Board top (cols 0-7): |   |########| |   |########| |   |########| |   |########| |   |########| |   |########| |  | FAILURE ANALYSIS: |   - 10/10 episodes died within 10 pieces (board fills too fast) |   - High variance: best=19 but mean=4.9 (inconsistent) |  | HYPOTHESIS PERFORMANCE: |   build_flat: win=30%, avg_reward=132.26, spec=0.42, evals=158 |   minimize_height: win=11%, avg_reward=130.47, spec=0.42, evals=158 |   maximize_lines: win=59%, avg_reward=134.61, spec=0.42, evals=158 |  | DREAMER STATUS: |   Reliance: 1.0 |   Dream interval: 1 |   Active options: 3 |   Best hypothesis: build_flat |  | QUESTIONS - Please respond with SPECIFIC actionable advice: |   1. Given the board state and failure pattern, what SPECIFIC |      placement strategy should we try? (e.g. 'prioritize filling |      column 3 gaps before building height elsewhere') |   2. Which hypothesis should we STOP using and why? |   3. Suggest a NEW micro-hypothesis in this format: |      'When [board condition], do [specific placement action]'"}],"timestamp":1771361326695}}
