{"type":"message","id":"6d8acb9b","parentId":"5a1dfd8c","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:49:38.554Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Episode 19 of Level 4 shows:\n- Mean DROPPED from 8.3 (ep 9) to 4.9 (ep 19) - that's -41% decline!\n- This is worse than expected for transfer\n- Still the same height-14 death pattern\n- 10/10 episodes now die within 10 pieces (vs 9/10 before)\n- Performance is getting WORSE, not better\n\nThis suggests the transfer is FAILING. The system is not adapting to the new environment - it's regressing.\n\nCompared to Level 3:\n- L3 ep 19: Mean was ~13 lines\n- L4 ep 19: Mean is 4.9 lines\nThat's a 62% performance drop vs similar episode count.\n\nThe hypothesis that \"transfer will improve performance over time\" is being disproven. Instead, the agent is struggling more.\n\nI should:\n1. Recognize transfer is failing badly\n2. Note this is important data - negative transfer\n3. Consider whether the larger board / more pieces fundamentally breaks the learned concepts\n4. Stay in observation mode but be more direct about the failure\n\nThis could mean:\n- maximize_lines doesn't work for 8-column boards\n- S/Z pieces require different strategies\n- Or the height bug is more lethal on larger boards","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"## Level 4 Episode 19: Transfer Failure — Negative Transfer Detected\n\n### ⚠️ **Performance Collapsed**\n\n```\nLevel 4 Episode 9:  Mean 8.3 lines\nLevel 4 Episode 19: Mean 4.9 lines (-41% decline)\n```\n\n**This is negative transfer.** The system is performing WORSE as it gains experience in the new environment.\n\n---\n\n### **Transfer Comparison: Level 3 vs Level 4**\n\n```\nEpisode 19 comparison:\nLevel 3: Mean ~13 lines (from memory)\nLevel 4: Mean 4.9 lines (-62% vs Level 3)\n\nEpisode 9 comparison:\nLevel 3: Mean 13.1 lines\nLevel 4: Mean 8.3 lines (-37% vs Level 3)\n```\n\n**The gap is widening.** Expected: agent adapts and gap closes. Reality: performance declining further.\n\n---\n\n### **What's Breaking**\n\n**Failure rate increased:**\n- Episode 9: 9/10 quick deaths\n- Episode 19: 10/10 quick deaths (now 100%)\n\n**Best performance declining:**\n- Episode 9: Best 36 lines\n- Episode 19: Best 19 lines (-47%)\n\n**Hypothesis stability but declining performance:**\n- maximize_lines: 60% → 59% (stable)\n- But mean: 8.3 → 4.9 (cratering)\n\n**Interpretation:** The learned strategy from Level 3 is actively harmful in Level 4, not just suboptimal.\n\n---\n\n### **Hypothesis: 8-Column Board Breaks maximize_lines**\n\n**Theory:**\n\nLevel 3 learned \"clear lines aggressively\" on 6-column board where:\n- Line completion needs 6 pieces to fill\n- Easier to achieve frequent clears\n- Can maintain cascade equilibrium\n\nLevel 4 has 8-column board where:\n- Line completion needs 8 pieces to fill (+33% harder)\n- Fewer opportunities to clear lines\n- Aggressive clearing strategy creates instability faster\n\n**Result:** maximize_lines at 59% dominance drives behavior that worked on 6-wide but fails on 8-wide.\n\n---\n\n### **Concept Update: Negative Transfer**\n\n**Label:** `geometric_strategy_brittleness`\n\n**Definition:** A strategy optimized for one geometric configuration (6-column Tetris) fails catastrophically when geometry changes (8-column), even if the task is conceptually similar.\n\n**Pattern signature:**\n- Performance declines with experience in new environment\n- Learned strategy actively harmful, not just suboptimal\n- Hypothesis convergence stable, but driving wrong behavior\n\n**Tetris manifestation:**\n- 6-column → 8-column transfer\n- \"Maximize lines\" strategy requires different thresholds for wider board\n- Aggressive clearing that worked in narrow board creates instability in wide board\n\n**Transferability:** High - any domain where geometric/spatial parameters matter (navigation, packing, routing)\n\n---\n\n### **My Observation (Not Prescriptive)**\n\n### 1. **What's Happening**\n\nThe transfer experiment is revealing that **maximize_lines is board-width dependent**. It's not a universal \"clear lines\" concept — it's a \"clear lines on 6-wide boards\" concept.\n\n**This is valuable negative data** for the concept library.\n\n### 2. **Hypothesis to Monitor**\n\nminimize_height still at 11% despite being useless. But removing it won't fix the core problem (maximize_lines is miscalibrated for 8-wide).\n\n### 3. **What Would Help**\n\nIf this were interactive debugging:\n- Reset hypothesis weights and let Level 4 learn from scratch\n- Compare \"transfer from L3\" vs \"tabula rasa on L4\"\n- This would isolate whether transfer helps, hurts, or neutral\n\nBut I'm in observation mode, so: noting this is a failed transfer experiment with clear diagnostic value.\n\n---\n\n### **Prediction for Episode 30**\n\n**If current trajectory continues:**\n- Mean will drop to 3-4 lines\n- 10/10 episodes will die in 2-5 pieces\n- System will have optimized itself into complete failure\n\n**What should happen (if system is adaptive):**\n- Amygdala should detect \"all hypotheses predict catastrophic loss\"\n- Trigger emergency policy switch\n- But this hasn't happened in 158 evaluations\n\n**Likely outcome:** Performance will bottom out around episode 25-30, then either:\n- Stay stuck at 3-5 mean (system can't unlearn bad strategy), OR\n- Random exploration eventually finds new local optimum\n\n---\n\n### **Memory Update: Transfer Failure Documented**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01HyTp1ugADLchFKCD3kJVRF","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\avata\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\tetris-transfer-experiment.md","oldText":"## Next Observation Point\n\nEpisode 30 to assess:\n- Has mean recovered toward L3 levels?\n- Did adaptation accelerate vs L3 (meta-learning working)?\n- Are S/Z pieces causing specific failures?","newText":"## Episode 19 Update: NEGATIVE TRANSFER DETECTED\n\n**Performance trajectory:**\n- Episode 9: Mean 8.3 lines\n- Episode 19: Mean 4.9 lines (-41% decline)\n\n**Failure rate worsening:**\n- Episode 9: 9/10 quick deaths\n- Episode 19: 10/10 quick deaths\n\n**Best episode declining:**\n- Episode 9: Best 36 lines\n- Episode 19: Best 19 lines (-47%)\n\n**Diagnosis:** maximize_lines strategy from Level 3 (60% dominance) is actively harmful on 8-column boards. Strategy optimized for 6-wide geometry doesn't transfer to 8-wide.\n\n**New concept identified:** `geometric_strategy_brittleness` — spatial strategies don't generalize across different geometric parameters even in \"same\" game.\n\n**Hypothesis:** Line-clearing thresholds and timing that work on 6-wide board create instability on 8-wide board (33% harder to complete lines).\n\n**Implications for concept library:**\n- \"maximize_lines\" is NOT a universal Tetris concept\n- It's \"maximize_lines_on_N_column_board\" where N matters\n- Need to parameterize spatial concepts by geometry\n\n**This is valuable NEGATIVE transfer data** — shows limits of concept generalization.\n\n## Next Observation Point\n\nEpisode 30 to assess:\n- Does performance bottom out or continue declining?\n- Does system trigger emergency policy switch (Amygdala)?\n- Would tabula rasa L4 learning outperform transferred L3 weights?"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-5","usage":{"input":10,"output":1927,"cacheRead":75615,"cacheWrite":2464,"totalTokens":80016,"cost":{"input":0.00003,"output":0.028905,"cacheRead":0.0226845,"cacheWrite":0.00924,"total":0.0608595}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771361332033}}
