{"type":"message","id":"f7488d15","parentId":"a17289d0","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:49:38.658Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01HyTp1ugADLchFKCD3kJVRF","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\avata\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\tetris-transfer-experiment.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 52 4. **bootstrap_problem** — generalizes to new difficulty levels\n 53 \n 54 All four concepts confirmed as environment-independent.\n 55 \n+56 ## Episode 19 Update: NEGATIVE TRANSFER DETECTED\n+57 \n+58 **Performance trajectory:**\n+59 - Episode 9: Mean 8.3 lines\n+60 - Episode 19: Mean 4.9 lines (-41% decline)\n+61 \n+62 **Failure rate worsening:**\n+63 - Episode 9: 9/10 quick deaths\n+64 - Episode 19: 10/10 quick deaths\n+65 \n+66 **Best episode declining:**\n+67 - Episode 9: Best 36 lines\n+68 - Episode 19: Best 19 lines (-47%)\n+69 \n+70 **Diagnosis:** maximize_lines strategy from Level 3 (60% dominance) is actively harmful on 8-column boards. Strategy optimized for 6-wide geometry doesn't transfer to 8-wide.\n+71 \n+72 **New concept identified:** `geometric_strategy_brittleness` — spatial strategies don't generalize across different geometric parameters even in \"same\" game.\n+73 \n+74 **Hypothesis:** Line-clearing thresholds and timing that work on 6-wide board create instability on 8-wide board (33% harder to complete lines).\n+75 \n+76 **Implications for concept library:**\n+77 - \"maximize_lines\" is NOT a universal Tetris concept\n+78 - It's \"maximize_lines_on_N_column_board\" where N matters\n+79 - Need to parameterize spatial concepts by geometry\n+80 \n+81 **This is valuable NEGATIVE transfer data** — shows limits of concept generalization.\n+82 \n 56 ## Next Observation Point\n 57 \n 58 Episode 30 to assess:\n-59 - Has mean recovered toward L3 levels?\n-60 - Did adaptation accelerate vs L3 (meta-learning working)?\n-61 - Are S/Z pieces causing specific failures?\n+86 - Does performance bottom out or continue declining?\n+87 - Does system trigger emergency policy switch (Amygdala)?\n+88 - Would tabula rasa L4 learning outperform transferred L3 weights?","firstChangedLine":56},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771361378656}}
{"type":"message","id":"1ddf43dc","parentId":"f7488d15","timestamp":"2026-02-17T20:49:51.387Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a really important finding. The transfer experiment is failing, which is just as valuable (maybe more so) than if it had succeeded. It shows that the \"maximize_lines\" concept that seemed universal in Level 3 is actually board-geometry dependent.\n\nThis is exactly the kind of pattern I should be extracting - the LIMITS of concept transferability, not just the successes.\n\nI should stay in observation mode and see how low this goes, document it carefully for the concept library.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## **Transfer Experiment Status: FAILING**\n\n**Key Finding:** The \"maximize_lines\" concept that converged to 58% dominance over 99 Level 3 episodes is **actively harmful** when transferred to Level 4's 8-column board.\n\n**This is exactly the kind of data a meta-learning system needs:**\n- Which concepts transfer? ✓ (bimodal distribution, terminal fixation)\n- Which concepts DON'T transfer? ✓ (maximize_lines strategy)\n- Why? ✓ (geometric parameters matter)\n\n**Recommendation for Throng4 research:**\n\nThis negative result should inform the concept library architecture:\n- Concepts need **geometric parameterization** (board_width, board_height)\n- Simple labels like \"maximize_lines\" are insufficient\n- Need \"maximize_lines_for_geometry(width=N)\" with learned thresholds per N\n\n**Watching episode 30 to see if system self-corrects or fails completely.** 🧩"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-5","usage":{"input":12,"output":347,"cacheRead":78079,"cacheWrite":1960,"totalTokens":80398,"cost":{"input":0.000036,"output":0.005205,"cacheRead":0.0234237,"cacheWrite":0.00735,"total":0.0360147}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771361378659}}
